{"TopicId":217204,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Seperate the controls for wheel throttle and pitch","CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-14T20:55:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-14T20:55:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrying to accelerate a rover that has a reaction wheen on it also pitches nose down casing the rover to try to somersault.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dr.phees","CreatedById":32383,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-15T11:45:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP 1 you could bind that to different keys. I always put wheel acceleration and steering to \u0022ijkl\u0022. Isn\u0027t that possible in 2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EvelynThe Dragon","CreatedById":227182,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-15T22:55:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684097711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tomf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/14/2023 at 1:55 PM, tomf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrying to accelerate a rover that has a reaction wheen on it also pitches nose down casing the rover to try to somersault.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can try disabling pitch control for the reaction wheel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-16T09:19:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684191314\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227182\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EvelynThe Dragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, EvelynThe Dragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can try disabling pitch control for the reaction wheel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat isn\u0027t actually an option in ksp2. And I do want to be able to control the pitch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EvelynThe Dragon","CreatedById":227182,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-16T18:00:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684228770\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tomf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, tomf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat isn\u0027t actually an option in ksp2. And I do want to be able to control the pitch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, crap, I thought you could do that. It would have its (somewhat rare) uses if you could disable pitch, yaw or roll for them.\u00A0 I am glad that is an option for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E, but that isn\u0027t applicable to your issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}